eason":null,"body":"Looking at https://examples.holoviz.org/gallery/ship_traffic/ship_traffic.html#interactive-plots I think it'd be helpful to include something like `legend = hv.util.create_legend(groups, cmap); legend * plot` or even simpler `hv.util.add_legend(plot, groups, cmap)`

```python
import pandas as pd
import hvplot.pandas
import colorcet as cc
import holoviews as hv

groups = {
    "A": "apple",
    "B": "banana",
    "C": "cherry",
}
colors = cc.glasbey_bw_minc_20_minl_30
color_key = {
    list(groups.keys())[i]: tuple(int(e * 255.0) for e in v)
    for i, v in enumerate(colors[: (len(groups))][::-1])
}
legend = hv.NdOverlay(
    {
        groups[k]: hv.Points([0, 0], label=str(groups[k])).opts(
            color=cc.rgb_to_hex(*v), size=0
        )
        for k, v in color_key.items()
    }
)
legend.options(xaxis="bare", yaxis="bare", title="", toolbar=None)
```","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/holoviz/holoviews/issues/6320/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/holoviz/holoviews/issues/6320/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/holoviz/holoviews/issues/comments/2219001927","html_url":"https://github.com/holoviz/holoviews/issues/6320#issuecomment-2219001927","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/holoviz/holoviews/issues/6320","id":2219001927,"node_id":"IC_kwDOASoy8M6EQ0hH","user":{"login":"jbednar","id":1695496,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE2OTU0OTY=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1695496?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jbednar","html_url":"https://github.com/jbednar","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jbednar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jbednar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jbednar/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jbednar/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jbednar/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jbednar/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jbednar/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jbednar/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jbednar/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2024-07-09T23:38:42Z","updated_at":"2024-07-09T23:38:42Z","author_association":"MEMBER","body":"This issue is arguably a duplicate of https://github.com/holoviz/holoviews/issues/6203 , which itself is a duplicate of https://github.com/holoviz/holoviews/issues/6052, or at least there wouldn't be much need for such a utility if those issues were addressed. Plus there's some issue somewhere (couldn't quickly fiind it) that acknowledges that we now do create a legend automatically in many cases, it's just not usable, so we end up with two legends (the fake one as in the code above, plus an auto-generated one). The problem with the auto-generated one is that for ship_traffic, it would show the category number rather than the string name, and for census it would show 'w' instead of 'White'.  So yes, a utility would be useful, but more useful in more cases would be to generate the key automatically, as long as we can accept a mapping dictionary from underlying category to displayed label.  With that I don't think the user would often need a fully custom utility, though of course we could write one for our own purposes for use with `datashade()` and then also expose that to the few users who do want to control it manually.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/holoviz/holoviews/issues/comments/2219001927/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null}}

